==English==

===Pronunciation===
* [[IPA]]: /jə/

===Pronoun===
'''ya'''

# ''(non-standard):'' [[you]]; used for writing or transcribing very informal speech peculiar to youthful speakers, typically containing many slang words.
#: ''Yo homes, smell '''ya''' later!''

===Usage note===
*'''ya''' is a frequent misspelling of [[yeah]] ''(non-standard slang for [[yes]].)''

----

==Spanish==
===Etymology===
Latin ''[[iam]]''

===Adverb===
'''ya'''
# [[now]]
# [[already]]
# in the [[near]] [[future]]; [[soon]]
# [[anymore]]; no [[longer]]
# ''[[emphatical]]''
#: ''¡ya lo se!'' - "I know!"

'''no ya'''
# not [[only]]

'''ya que'''
# [[since]]; now that

====Synonyms====
*[[ahora]] (1)
*[[ahorita]] (1, ''colloquial'')

===Conjunction===
'''ya ... ya'''
# [[first]] ''this'' [[then]] ''that''
#: ''¡ya lluvia ya nieve!'' - "first rain now snow!"
# [[whether]] ''this'' [[or]] ''that''
#: ''ya sol ya lluvia'' - "whether sun or rain"
 
